caption: Food was good.  Usually is so really nothing to comment about that.  Will eat again.  But less two stars for slow service and online only orders.  What used to be a quick in and out pick up is now a 10-15 minute wait, and that is only if they have the food ready on time.  Took an extra 5 minutes for the food to be ready.  In reality not bad, but still inconvenient when you shut down in person ordering and you don't have the order ready when you said you will.  Edit:. And now that I have gotten home I would also like to add there is no point asking for our names in the order if you are not going to lable which is which.

DON'T EAT HERE....what a gong show this place is. Their online ordering system means they are taking way more orders than they can make. Took 50 minutes to make two regular salad bowls, even though the system said it would take 20 minutes.  It is now just a small building full of upset, hungry people. Social distancing is about 6 inches. What a mess and horrible management. They also announced they are out of rice. Lol This will be the last visit from us.

HORRIBLE SERVICE! I am appalled by everything this location did! We ordered online and went to pick it up and they didn't make our order. They got it and said that they didn't make it. We waited another 15 min for 2 entrees and some chips. They didn't even make us what we ordered! I had to scrape out the good portion of my vegan bowl because they put cheese in it. Thankfully my boyfriend eats anything but his order was wrong as well. Never ordering here again.

I moved away for a couple years and never had a problem here, until this month when I moved back. The first order was basically a half bowl! I mean hardly anything in it. So the next time I ordered, I asked for extra everything, including extra fajitas, but there were NONE! Both my friend's bowl and mine had hardly any sofritas, and while my bowl was normal portion, she had, again, a half bowl! Not to mention, when I picked it up at 12:45, they were out of dressing. I mean, come one, that is the main ingredient for their salad's to make it a SALAD! I could understand if it was late at night, but the middle of lunch service? Really? The gal was nice and made it up to me. But I would have rather had the dressing. With no dressing or fajitas, my meal was dry and boring. Over all, this location is flailing - giving customers tiny portions because they are carrying out and won't discover until they are home (or in my case, 2.5 hours away)! Shame on you, Chipotle.

This happened 01/30/21, I hate leaving negative reviews but this takes the cake. A friend and I created an online order with the app around 8:15 pm. The app said our order would be complete around 8:30pm. Okay, sounds good. We got there at the approximate time. We ended up waiting 20 additional minutes for customers who walked in to be served first and 1 person who also ordered online or phone. I overheard the worker saying that there was no lettuce for the rest of the night to said walk-in customers. Okay, weird but it happens. So after they finished the last person in line, we jump in line to inquire about our order and they promptly started making the order for us. 1 person was working the front alone, with 2 more employees in the back doing who knows what (didn't even know they were there until the popped out 10 mins into our wait), there was also another having a break in the corner, all the while another employee was working on the beverage area, we no idea it was being taken down, it's around the corner out of eye shot. We had ordered the lemonade and hibiscus lemonade with our app order. Lo and behold, the lemonade and tea area had already been taken down by the time we got our order.  We ordered tortillas on the side and they were not even cooked all the way, they still smelled of uncooked flour. We didn't even finish the meal, it was terrible at best. This was the roughest experience I've had in a while anywhere. Beware of this Chipotle. And I thought they closed at 10pm, why was everything being taken down so early?

She got a veggie bowl with random pieces of chicken with white rice. I double checked my order. We put in the correct items. The workers just know that we're not gonna drive all the way back to complain so they don't bother getting the orders right. It's a rude thing to do.

The last 3 visits have resulted in burritos that were inedible. The burritos were so poorly assembled and wraped that the ingredients were spewing forth into the foil. (The foil was the only properly wrapped portion of my entire purchase and was probably done with care to mask the sheer calamity contained inside) To make matters worse, all the ingredients of the burrito were layered in segments. With pico occupying the very end of my burrito, the chicken slammed into the middle section, and sour cream on the other end. Lastly, there was no effort on the staffs part to provide a plate or container or plastic-ware to eat the soggy flop fest that was supposed to be my burrito.
